Package de.muspellheim.commons.time

Class LocalDateTimeInterval

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.muspellheim.commons.time.LocalDateTimeInterval
  • public final class LocalDateTimeInterval
extends Object
    Interval between two times based on LocalDateTime.

    Intervals are inclusive of the start and exclusive of the end.

      • parse

        public static LocalDateTimeInterval parse​(@NonNull
                                          @NonNull CharSequence text)
        Obtains an instance of DateTimeInterval from a text string such as 2007-12-03T10:15:30.

        The string must represent a valid interval and is parsed using DateTimeFormatter.ISO_LOCAL_DATE_TIME.

        Parameters:
        text - the text to parse such as "2019-08-16T17:02/2019-09-09T08:50", not null
        Returns:
        the parsed local date-time interval, not null
        Throws:
        DateTimeParseException - if the text cannot be parsed
